<TEXT>
a roman catholic candidate for the state 
legislature has been asked to resign from the parish council of his 
church because he supports womens right to abortion 
monsignor william odonnell of our lady of lourdes church in 
bethesda md said monday he had already accepted the resignation 
of john hurson who is seeking election in a district where 
abortion is a major campaign issue 
hurson denied that he had resigned 
odonnell said he asked hurson to quit the parish council 
because his position was contrary to the teachings of the 
church 
its as simple as that whats the big deal odonnell said 
hurson said he opposes abortions but does not believe the state 
should pass laws against abortion 
richard dowling spokesmen for the maryland catholic conference 
said this was the first time a public official or candidate in 
maryland or the district of columbia had been disciplined for 
taking a prochoice stand on abortion 
hurson criticized church officials for trying to quell dissent 
on the abortion issue 
it seems to me that catholics need to have if they are going 
to serve in public office the freedom to represent everyone not 
just the catholic hierarchy he said 
i want to participate fully in my church and the inability 
to do that is very painful one should not have to put ones 
religion in low gear just because you decided to run for public 
office he said 
hurson a lawyer is running as a democrat on a ticket headed by 
patricia sher one of the leaders of the abortion rights forces in 
the maryland house of delegates 
sher is giving up her house seat to run in the primary against 
democratic state sen margaret schweinhaut who supported a 
filibuster in the senate last march that blocked passage of a 
strong prochoice law 
hurson said he talked with odonnell twice last week to discuss 
his abortion stance he was told friday that he would have to 
resign 
i told him you realize theres going to be some publicity 
about this hurson said he said oh yes 
</TEXT>
