<TEXT>
call it just us folks this new weekly 
program on cable television channels across the country but it 
wont be a ratings threat to the simpsons or to americas 
funniest home videos 
this show is intentionally mundane 
rep dave mccurdy dokla and a band of moderate democrats say 
they will take to the house floor regularly to correct what they 
say is a public misperception the mainstream forum as they 
call themselves hopes to show that democrats are plain folks not 
what mccurdy derisively calls the screamers of the extreme 
right and left 
i might even talk about my kids making the allstar team in 
baseball or softball he said 
the idea is to show voters that their democratic congressmen are 
much like themselves calm thoughtful people who share their 
concerns about tax fairness crime budget reality and the 
countrys security he said 
we will not be as wild in our rhetoric or as provocative or 
daring or outright hostile mccurdy added we are not going to 
disparage individuals or personalities thats part of the 
message we want to show people were not extreme were not 
crazy 
joining him will be lawmakers like barbara kennelly of 
connecticut john spratt of south carolina mike espy of 
mississippi louise slaughter of new york and tim penny of 
minnesota 
mccurdy and his allies are members of the democratic leadership 
council an organization of moderatetoconservative democrats 
formed to try to move the party toward the right into what they 
see as the countrys mainstream 
the idea of using the house floor and its video connection to 
hundreds of thousands of viewers after business hours first came 
to the republicans it was newt gingrich and his conservative 
opportunity society who began staging issues discussions in 1984 
democrats thought it was silliness thenspeaker thomas p 
tip oneills response was to order the tv cameras to pan the 
chamber and show that the intenselooking gop debaters were 
actually speaking to an empty house 
but the televised mock debates did have an impact democrats 
were portrayed night after night as not caring about issues like 
the federal budget deficit and ignoring matters such as school 
prayer abortion and the lineitem veto and they began to be 
concerned that people might actually believe it 
the partys next response soon abandoned was to consider a gag 
order that would limit how many hours could be devoted to the 
afterhours talkfests known as special orders in the 
meantime gingrich of georgia rode his tv visibility to become 
house gop whip the no 2 leadership position 
later an informal group of democratic activists mostly 
liberals began meeting to define and refine a public message for 
the party they worked mostly through newspaper reporters 
columnists and tv commentators however 
then mccurdy and about a dozen other democratic moderates 
decided it was time to fight fire with fire and won the 
acceptance if not the blessing of speaker thomas s foley dwash 
weve got news for the minority whip and his minions 
mccurdy announced in the maiden broadcast late last month their 
free ride is over were not going to let them define us anymore 
nor the oklahoman added in an interview will that job be left to 
party liberals or interest groups 
that mccurdy should now seize upon using the house floor 
available in more than 50 million homes through the cspan cable 
network is taken as a compliment by gingrich he even hopes the 
two opposing sides can be turned into a kind of pointcounterpoint 
we always thought that something like our use of cspan was 
inevitable and it was good that its healthy gingrich said 
weve always encouraged democrats to come over and debate because 
its just a lot more fun 
we are basically taking a page out of gingrichs book 
mccurdy concedes im of a different generation than oneill 
who brushed aside the gop tv tactic cable tv has become a 
powerful voice 
