reflecting herd rebuilding and recovery from last years drought 
and herd liquidations 
last week usda estimated meat imports in the 1990 calendar year 
at 116 billion pounds compared with slightly more than 114 
billion pounds in 1989 the estimate covers meat primarily beef 
and veal subject to annual quota restrictions if it appears 
imports will exceed a trigger level 
the trigger for 1990 is more than 136 billion pounds meaning 
that actual imports probably will fall far short 
about a dozen countries supply quotatype meat to the us 
market but australia and new zealand are the main providers 
