mumia abujamal of philadelphia is on pennsylvanias death row 
for the fatal 1981 shooting of a white police officer he was 
convicted in 1982 and exhausted his state court appeals last year 
his latest appeal petition filed in may is pending before the 
supreme court 
the case has become the rallying cry for opponents of the 
racist death penalty said rachel wolkenstein staff attorney for 
the new yorkbased partisan defense committee organizer of 
protests staged in london new york paris hamburg east berlin 
and toronto 
