production as unprofitable businesses go bankrupt 
figures on how much money would begin to stabilize the economy 
range from 5 to 20 billion colossal compared to what eastern 
european countries received to restructure their economies but 
modest given the size of the soviet economy and its relatively low 
level of foreign debt 
