<TEXT>
president mikhail s gorbachev won a critical 
behindthescenes struggle today for a new communist party 
politburo that is expected to champion his reforms and push for a 
looser federation of the soviet republics 
the party congress voted to require the politburo to consist of 
the general secretary his deputy and the first secretaries of the 
parties of the 15 republics 
the change guarantees that the small group of primarily russian 
men who traditionally ruled the soviet union would be replaced by 
largely proreform nonrussian communists 
most of the republic party leaders want the political 
sovereignty market economy and looser union of states advocated by 
gorbachev 
the change also allows gorbachev to bypass the 250member 
central committee expected to be heavily conservative when the 
congress elects it later this week 
the congress is expected to elect gorbachev to continue as 
general secretary despite vitriolic criticism of his political and 
economic reforms from delegates at the largely conservative party 
congress 
some delegates said he may be allowed to virtually handpick his 
deputy although the congress officially elects the person when it 
meets once in five years 
a wearylooking gorbachev took the floor of the 28th party 
congress this afternoon after hammering his proposal through four 
hours of heated discussions in committee 
after making his announcement gorbachev sat down next to the 
temporary chairman of the party congress parliamentary chairman 
anatoly lukyanov and urged quietly lets vote 
the key vote on changing the politburo membership to include the 
republic leaders was 3325 to 839 
gorbachev told delegates that others could be added to the 
politburo by the central committee from among its members but the 
final rules did not mention this 
the new rule could completely change the politburo membership 
because none of the 15 republic party chiefs are now members of the 
12man body 
seven of the 12 men on the current politburo already have said 
they will resign or have hinted of the possibility 
any decentralization and particularly the looser union of 
sovereign republics now under discussion would give the republics 
more power over their own affairs 
most republic leaders also believe their areas will fare far 
better under a market economy than under continued central 
planning which they blame for sucking dry their republics 
resources and giving little in return 
gorbachev said the new structure would allow the 15 republic 
parties to act independently and to really influence the central 
committee and politburo 
the current 12man politburo has only two nonrussian members 
foreign minister eduard shevardnadze from the republic of georgia 
and ukrainian president vladimir ivashko there is but one 
nonrussian latvian boris pugo among the seven nonvoting members 
of the politburo 
the congress was expected to take nominations for general 
secretary later in the day 
on sunday gorbachev who has been the party general secretary 
since 1985 faced tough questioning at a meeting of workers and 
farmers attending the congress as nonvoting observers 
many soviets blame the communists for the economic crisis and 
decades of institutional corruption and the partys candidates 
have suffered defeat after defeat at the polls 
coal miners announced plans to stage a oneday nationwide strike 
wednesday to warn party leaders they can no longer take for granted 
the support of the working class they claim to represent 
the meeting of workers farmers and gorbachev was closed to 
foreign reporters and soviet media carried no details 
many of gorbachevs remarks were conveyed by nina zhukova a 
weaver from the russian city of ivanovo she said she sat near 
gorbachev at the meeting her account was confirmed by other 
participants interviewed on red square 
sergei sotnikov a party official from yaroslavl said the 
atmosphere was tense and included complaints about the lack of 
consumer goods in stores 
they criticize me personally or the politburo and debate 
whether to remove us or not gorbachev reportedly said during 
the fourhour session 
i will listen to it all but you will decide everything am i 
needed by you you will decide he said 
