on top of other food purchases such as sugar meat tea bread 
and vegetables she must pay rent for her small suburban house and 
bus fares to work and back leaving her without a cent to spare 
her two brothers like most unemployed zambians try to make 
ends meet by selling smuggled goods from botswana and south africa 
on lusakas black market 
