dismay with the president 
however kaunda has refused to make any significant concessions 
instead he promised to crack down on coup plotters and 
thugs some 5000 students from the university of zambia who 
led the week of violence have been sent home 
but kaunda did seize on the troubles to announce a national 
referendum on whether to revive political pluralism 
the ruling united national independence party grudgingly agreed 
to put the issue to a vote in march but only after kaunda declared 
he feared democracy would plunge the country into tribal conflicts 
if the referendum is free and fair zambians are expected to 
snub their head of state and opt for the multiparty system used by 
the british colonists prior to independence observers say 
