april by the national interprofessional office of wine which 
represents various associations of winemakers and sellers 
participants were asked about the drinking habits of all adults 
in their household and the responses reflected the practices of 
12400 people the organization said no margin of error was given 
in a 1980 survey conducted by the group 387 percent of the 
respondents said they never drink wine that percentage climbed to 
451 in 1985 and to 507 this year 
wine consumption varies sharply by sex according to the survey 
it said 109 percent of the women and 281 percent of the men 
identified themselves as daily wine drinkers 
asked why they didnt drink wine 734 percent of the 
respondents said they didnt like it and 253 percent cited health 
concerns 
