all of the automobiles for the 11day gm sunrayce usa were 
designed and built by college engineering students from the united 
states and canada at costs ranging from about 30000 to more than 
1 million 
the cars are powered strictly by the sun and solarenergy 
storage batteries 
the winner will have the lowest elapsed time over secondary 
roads in eight states the race is in daily stages with each car 
starting at the same point each day it ends july 19 at the general 
motors technical center outside detroit 
