the soviet union facing a lack of fuel for 
domestic use will cut its oil exports by 140000 barrels a day 
according to premier nikolai i ryzhkov 
the soviet union is the worlds largest oil producer although 
production levels have been declining the us government 
estimated 1989 total soviet oil output at 1214 million barrels per 
day 
production has fallen because of the cost of maintaining output 
as well as ethnic unrest in oil producing regions such as 
azerbaijan 
ryzhkov said the government decided in late june to cut its oil 
exports by 7 million metric tons or 140000 barrels a day 
the cut in exports would apply to socialist bloc countries as 
well as western nations he said saturday answering questions by 
delegates to the 28th communist party congress on the upcoming 
soviet harvest 
this will permit us to supply our agriculture ryzhkov said 
adding that otherwise fuel shortages would hurt the harvest 
