churchs official indian council the indians are tired of 
declarations that dont bring change 
collor who took office in march has vowed to defend indian 
rights in april he ordered the destruction of clandestine landing 
strips on yanomani lands that are used by amazon gold miners 
the yanomani live on brazils northwest frontier with venezuela 
thousands of miners invaded their territory after large reserves of 
gold diamonds and other minerals were found there in 1987 
brand dismissed the dynamiting of the landing strips as a 
publicity stunt 
only 14 of over 100 strips were destroyed and the majority 
have already been recovered by the miners he said 
brand said the churchs indian council wants the government to 
remove all gold miners from the region and revoke decrees issued by 
former president jose sarneys government which created mining 
reserves on yanomani territory 
the negligence of collors government in the face of this 
problem makes it coresponsible for the yanomani genocide he 
said 
he said the yanomanis situation was rapidly worsening and 
medical care and food supplies were desperately needed 
miners have disrupted the yanomanis hunting and fishing 
polluted rivers with mercury used to clean gold and brought 
diseases previously unknown to the indians 
many tribes have been hard hit by malnutrition venereal 
diseases and malaria introduced by the outsiders other 
tribespeople have died in clashes with miners 
brand said 15 percent of the yanomani population estimated at 
9000 has disappeared in less than three years 
