detained more than 2000 people throughout the metropolitan area 
who were not carrying documents 
on may 14 a column of 300 mrta rebels seized the northern 
jungle town of saposoa freeing 35 suspected guerrillas from the 
towns jail and robbing three banks 
the mrta takes its name from an 18th century mestizo or mixed 
blood revolutionary who led a peasant revolt against spanish 
colonial rule in the andes 
it is smaller and less radical than the maoist shining path 
guerrilla group which has been fighting since 1980 the government 
says more than 18500 people have died in the decade of political 
violence including police soldiers rebels government officials 
and civilians 
