under a bright sunny sky 29 
solarpowered cars designed and built by college students today 
began a 1600mile race from florida to detroit mich in efforts 
to prove a future technology 
the start of the 11day race sponsored by the department of 
energy the society of automative engineers and general motors was 
led by the first three qualifiers from the univerities of 
maryland michigan and mankato state in minnesota 
we hope young people will get excited about this race and 
that it serves as an incentive for future technology said gm 
president bob stemple in ceremonies before the start 
thirtytwo cars entered the competition but arizona state had 
