britain on monday denied it was about to link the 
pound to the exchange rate mechanism covering other major european 
currencies 
sterling strengthened in foreign exchange on speculation that 
such an announcement would be made at the houston summit in late 
new york trading the pound was quoted at 18065 up from late 
fridays 17865 
i can assure you that i am not going to announce this morning 
that britain is about to join the exchange rate mechanism john 
major britains chancellor of the exchequer told a news 
conference 
major speaking shortly before the opening of the summit of the 
worlds seven top industrialized nations reiterated that britains 
conditions for joining the exchange rate mechanism were unchanged 
britain promised in principle last summer to join the mechanism 
when its inflation rate now nearly 10 percent and among the 
highest in the european community falls other conditions about 
free capital movements in the community largely have been met 
the exchange rate mechanism links nine of the 12 currencies of 
the european community it is designed to prevent wide fluctuations 
in exchange rates 
earlier major met jacques delors president of the communitys 
executive commission to press britains alternative plan to 
delors radical proposals for a single european community currency 
president delors made it clear the commission is seriously 
examining our proposals said major 
the british proposal is for a new hard european currency the 
european currency unit or ecu to circulate alongside the 
communitys present currencies at present the ecu is used 
primarily as an accounting mechanism 
britain announced the plan last month a special conference is 
due to open in december and is supposed to make final decisions by 
the end of 1992 the year internal ec trade barriers are to be 
dismantled 
the delors program calls for a single central banking system as 
well as one currency britain says it never will agree to the 
delors plan because it means surrendering national control over its 
economy 
