a french investor accused of insider trading 
on rorer group inc securities has settled the charges with federal 
officials the securities and exchange commission announced monday 
without admitting or denying wrongdoing robert rossi agreed to 
pay nearly 145 million in alleged illegal profits plus interest 
the settlement was approved by a federal judge in new york on 
july 3 
rossi who maintains a mailing address in geneva switzerland 
was accused with three foreign companies last january of trading on 
inside information about merger talks between rorer a fort 
washington penn pharmaceutical company and another company 
later identified as frances rhonepoulenc sa 
daniel a pollack an attorney for rossi in new york said his 
client was pleased with the settlement and takes the position 
that his investment decision was based on his own analyses of rorer 
and other drug stocks the fact that the commission did not 
penalize him but only required him to disgorge his profits is some 
indication that the sec would have a difficult time proving the 
charges agasinst him in a courtroom 
