<TEXT>
digital equipment corp which is suffering from 
sluggish earnings announced a new midrange computer line monday 
designed to provide desktop computer users with more flexibility 
the computer line called vax 4000 is designed to compete 
directly with computers offered by international business machines 
corp digital unveiled the products at its annual decworld sales 
exposition here 
the new line is based on clientserver computing which allows 
one or more computers to act as control centers for networks of 
desktop machines 
in the 90s people want to use computers in a much more 
effective way said kenneth olsen digitals president 
digital says the vax 4000 delivers more power than ibms popular 
as400 minicomputer at half the cost digital is the worlds 
secondlargest computer company behind ibm 
users want to sit at the desktop of their choice olsen 
said they want the flexibility to quickly access information in 
any database on the network use the right application to get their 
work done and share the work they do with anyone else who needs 
it 
digital estimates there is a potential clientserver market of 
more than 100 billion over the next five years as the networked 
style of computing spreads from the office to the laboratory to the 
factory 
the vax 4000 announcement follows a fiscal year in which digital 
reported sluggish earnings the company based in the suburb of 
maynard has offered voluntary severance to thousands of employees 
to reduce its work force 
digital has not reported its fourthquarter earnings for the 
fiscal year ended june 30 but the company said last month that 
external forecasts of its fourthquarter earnings were too 
optimistic 
in the quarter that ended march 31 digital earned 249 
million or 20 cents a share compared with 256 million or 205 
per share during the same period a year earlier 
