<TEXT>
mitsubishi trust and banking corp said tuesday it 
will form a joint venture with chicago research amp trading group 
ltd one of the united states leading futures and options traders 
the joint venture with 150 million in startup capital will 
enable mitsubishi trust to join major european and us option 
trading exchanges such as those in chicago and philadelphia 
mitsubishi officials said 
the deal appears to mark a rare case of a japanese financial 
institution taking an active managgement and policy making role in 
a joint venture with an american financial institution 
in addition japanese firms in the past have not joined forces 
with any us firms that deal strictly with futures and options in 
the united states 
toshihiro hayashi of mitsubishi trusts bond and money market 
division said the joint venture as yet unnamed will be formed 
later this year the project is awaiting approval from japans 
finance ministry and the us government 
he said the joint venture would strengthen the credit standing 
of the chicagobased firm one of the worlds largest arbitrage 
trading firms a member of 20 exchanges worldwide 
arbitrage trading refers to buying currency commercial bills or 
securities in one market and selling them at the same time in 
another market to reap profits on the price discrepancy 
the joint venture is to be based in chicago and have offices in 
tokyo london new york and philadelphia it will pursue arbitrage 
trading primarily in currencies and interest raterelated products 
on major exchanges and on overthecounter markets 
mitsubishi trust is contributing most of the startup capital 
while chicago research is contributing expertise and both companies 
will contribute personnel officials said other terms of the joint 
venture were not disclosed 
</TEXT>
